text: Dennis Ruprecht is a New Hampshire politician serving in the New Hampshire House of Representatives. Ruprecht sits on the House Committee on Fish and Game and Marine Resources. He assumed office on December 5, 2018. His current term ends on December 4, 2020. ==Early life and education== Ruprecht graduated from Woodsville High School and currently attends Plymouth State University. ==Personal life== Ruprecht resides in Landaff, New Hampshire. ==Electoral history== Ruprecht ran for election to the New Hampshire House of Representatives to represent Grafton 15. He won in the general election on November 6, 2018, as a 19-year-old. Ruprecht is running for re-election to the New Hampshire House of Representatives to represent Grafton 3. ==National politics== Ruprecht was selected as one of seventeen speakers to jointly deliver the keynote address at the 2020 Democratic National Convention. ==References== Category:21st-century American politicians Category:Living people Category:Members of the New Hampshire House of Representatives Category:New Hampshire Democrats Category:Plymouth State University alumni Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
